  <div id="about" class="page-section clearfix">
    <div class="container">
      <section class="content clearfix">
        
        <div class="gradient clearfix">

  <div class="grid-50 tablet-80">



    <h1>What is the Urban Observatory?</h1>
    
    <p>The Urban Observatory is an interactive exhibit that gives you the chance to compare and contrast data from cities around the world–all from one location. It aims to make the world’s data both understandable and useful. Brought to life by <strong>Richard Saul Wurman</strong>, <strong>RadicalMedia</strong>, and <strong>Esri</strong>, it is the first exhibit of its kind.</p>
    
      <!--<p>See it at the <a href="http://www.esri.com/uc">Esri User Conference</a><span class="txt-red">.</span></p>-->
     
    <!--<p>Experience it early 2015 at the <br /><b> <a href="http://www.si.edu">Smithsonian Institution</a> Smithsonian Institution</b>.</p>-->
    
    <p>Coming early 2015 to the Smithsonian Institution. <a href="http://www.urbanobservatory.org/preview" class="txt-red">Get a sneak peek today!</a></p>
     
    <h3 class="txt-inline">Intrigued?</h3>
    <!-- <a href="http://events.esri.com/info/uo/index.cfm" class="button green">Get Involved</a> -->
    <a class="button ctaButton">Get Involved</a>
  
  </div>
</div>
      
      </section>
    </div>
